x4freetext: A target of 5.41 mg/cm2 carbon was
prepared on an 0.8 mg/cm2 backing.
Gamma ray detection in activation measurement
and neutron TOF for neutron groups.
Two methods were employed to
deduce reaction cross sections: by observation of
neutron groups and by the 13N activity generated
simultaneously.

x4freetext: The error in the activation measurements
arises from decomposition of the complex decay curve
for annihilation radiation and correction for
possible 12C(p,gamma)13N activity.

The angular distributions of the ground state
neutron group were integrated from 0 to 180 degrees
by extrapolation, since data are available between 10
and 145 degree only.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The absolute error in the neutron yield
measurements is associated with the neutron detector
efficiency calibration which was made with an n-p
recoil spectrometer at Los Alamos.
For the 22.8 MeV case the error in the
integrated cross section because of uncertainty in
assumed cross sections is not more than 3% and at 16.3
MeV not more than 5%.
